# =============================================================================
# Spearyx Jobs — Environment Reference
# =============================================================================
# This application uses Cloudflare Workers bindings exclusively for secrets
# and infrastructure. There are no traditional environment variables for
# API keys or database credentials — all runtime config is in wrangler.toml.
#
# To provision required resources before first deploy:
#
#   1. D1 database (already exists):
#      wrangler d1 create spearyx-jobs
#
#   2. KV namespace (sessions + scrape cache):
#      wrangler kv namespace create spearyx-sessions
#      → Copy the returned `id` into wrangler.toml [[kv_namespaces]]
#
#   3. R2 bucket (generated PDFs):
#      wrangler r2 bucket create spearyx-documents
#
#   4. AI binding:
#      Declared in wrangler.toml [ai] — no provisioning needed.
#
#   5. Browser Rendering:
#      Declared in wrangler.toml [browser] — requires Workers Paid plan.
#
# =============================================================================
# Wrangler binding names (set in wrangler.toml, not here)
# =============================================================================
#
#   DB      = D1Database       (SQLite via Drizzle ORM)
#   KV      = KVNamespace      (session tokens, URL scrape cache)
#   R2      = R2Bucket         (PDF document storage)
#   AI      = Ai               (Workers AI — Llama 3.3 70B + Qwen 3 30B)
#   BROWSER = Fetcher          (Browser Rendering API for job scraping)
#
# =============================================================================
# Local development overrides (optional)
# =============================================================================
#
# NODE_ENV=development
